ENTRY            C3124   20260318   20260518   20260518       C257
SUBENT        C3124001   20260318   20260518   20260518       C257
BIB                 11         33
TITLE      Detailed View at Magnetic Dipole Strengths: The Case
           of Semimagic 50Ti
AUTHOR     (B.Kelly,M.Spieker,U.Friman-Gayer,L.T.Baby,T.Beck,
           A.L.Conley,S.W.Finch,J.Isaak,Krishichayan,
           E.Litvinova,H.Pai,N.Pietralla,D.Savran,W.Tornow,
           N.Tsoneva,A.Volya,V.Werner)
REFERENCE  (J,PRL,136,082502,2026)
           #doi:10.1103/82y9-svrd
INSTITUTE  (1USAFSU,2GERTHD,1USADKE,1USATNL,1USAWMU,2GERGSI,
           3RUMBUC)
FACILITY   (VDGT,1USAFSU) 9-MV Super-FN Tandem Van de Graaff
           accelerator at the John D. Fox Superconducting Linear
           Accelerator Laboratory of Florida State University.
DETECTOR   (MAGSP) The Super-Enge Split-Pole Spectrograph(SE-SPS).
SAMPLE     A self-supporting 49Ti metal foil of areal density
           rho=413 microg/cm2.
METHOD     Protons were detected and their momenta analyzed by
           the position-sensitive focal-plane detector of the
           SE-SPS. An average energy resolution of 50 keV (FWHM)
           was achieved. Differential cross sections,
           dsigma/domega, were measured at laboratory scattering
           angles ranging from 15 to 60 degrees. Through a
           comparison to well-established reaction calculations
           with FRESCO using the adiabatic distorted wave
           approximation (ADWA) and global optical model
           potentials, the angular-momentum, l, transfers through
           which excited states of 50Ti were populated in the
            (d,p) reaction were determined.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Statistical plus 15 % systematic
           uncertainty due to beam current integration.
           (ERR-SYS) Systematic uncertainty.
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by M.Spieker on April 1, 2026.
HISTORY    (20260318C) BP
ENDBIB              33
COMMON               2          3
EN         ERR-SYS
MEV        PER-CENT
       16.0       15.0
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           40
SUBENT        C3124002   20260318   20260518   20260518       C257
BIB                  2          4
REACTION   (22-TI-49(D,P)22-TI-50,PAR,DA)
STATUS     (TABLE,,B.Kelly+,J,PRL,136,082502,2026) Supplement,
           Fig. - 5. Data were provided by M.Spieker on March 31,
           2026.
ENDBIB               4
